HmAgentPortMask.name: HmAgentPortMask
HmAgentPortMask.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0' When setting this value, the system will ignore configuration for ports not between the first and last valid ports. Configuration of any port numbers between this range that are not valid ports return a failure message, but will still apply configuration for valid ports.

Note: Changing the timeout value for active sessions does not become effective until the session is reaccessed. Any keystroke will also activate the new timeout duration.

hmAgentSwitchBroadcastControlMode.name: hmAgentSwitchBroadcastControlMode
hmAgentSwitchBroadcastControlMode.description: The switch config broadcast allows you to enable or disable broadcast storm recovery mode. When you specify Enable for Broadcast Storm Recovery and the broadcast traffic on any Ethernet port exceeds 20 percent of the link speed, the switch blocks (discards) the broadcast traffic until the broadcast traffic returns to 10 percent or less. Upper limit for 10M link is 20% and lower limit is 10%. For 100M link Upper limit is 5% and lower limit is 2%

A value of zero indicates an infinite timeout, i.e. the entries in the list will not expire.

hmAgentSwitchIGMPSnoopingPortMask.name: hmAgentSwitchIGMPSnoopingPortMask
hmAgentSwitchIGMPSnoopingPortMask.description: IGMP Snooping Port Mask. This allows configuration of IGMP Snooping on selected ports. IGMP Snooping cannot be enabled on an interface that has routing enabled, or is a member of a LAG. If a port which has IGMP Snooping enabled becomes enabled for routing, or is enlisted as a member of a LAG, IGMP Snooping functionality will be disabled on that port. IGMP Snooping functionality will be subsequently be reenabled if routing is disabled or LAG membership is removed from an interface that had previously had IGMP Snooping enabled. To obtain port numbers from interface numbers, use the objects hmAgentPortDot1dBasePort and hmAgentPortIfIndex in the hmAgentPortConfigTable table.

hmAgentTransferUploadMode.name: hmAgentTransferUploadMode
hmAgentTransferUploadMode.description: Transfer upload mode configures the mode to use when uploading from the switch. The mode is either X/Y/ZMODEM or TFTP. X/Y/ZMODEM is valid only when the file transfer is initiated by the serial EIA 232 port.

hmAgentTransferUploadServerIP.name: hmAgentTransferUploadServerIP
hmAgentTransferUploadServerIP.description: Transfer upload tftpserverip configures the IP address of the server where the file is located. It is valid only when the Transfer Mode is TFTP. The address is 4 integer bytes ranging from 0 to 255.

hmAgentTransferUploadPath.name: hmAgentTransferUploadPath
hmAgentTransferUploadPath.description: Transfer upload tftppath configures the directory path where the file is to be uploaded to. The switch remembers the last file path used.

hmAgentTransferUploadFilename.name: hmAgentTransferUploadFilename
hmAgentTransferUploadFilename.description: Transfer upload tftpfilename configures the file name for the file being uploaded from the switch. It can be up to 32 alphanumeric characters. The switch remembers the last file name used. File path can be appended to the file name if the string is less than 17 characters. Otherwise, the File Path field will need to be used and the File Name will be appended to the File Path as is. An example would be File Path set to c:/tftp/code/ and File Name set to e1r1v1.opr. Note: File Name, File Path, and TFTP Server IP Address are applicable only if the Transfer Mode is TFTP.

hmAgentTransferUploadDataType.name: hmAgentTransferUploadDataType

hmAgentTransferDownloadServerIP.name: hmAgentTransferDownloadServerIP

hmAgentTransferDownloadPath.name: hmAgentTransferDownloadPath

hmAgentTransferDownloadFilename.name: hmAgentTransferDownloadFilename

Otherwise, the File Path field will need to be used and the File Name will be appended to the File Path as is. An example would be File Path set to c:/tftp/code/ and File Name set to e1r1v1.opr. Note: File Name, File Path, and TFTP Server IP Address are applicable only if the Transfer Mode is TFTP.

hmAgentTransferDownloadDataType.name: hmAgentTransferDownloadDataType

hmAgentPortDefaultType.name: hmAgentPortDefaultType
hmAgentPortDefaultType.description: This object identifies the default administrative port type, to be used in conjunction with the operational port type denoted by hmAgentPortType. The set of possible values for this object is the same as the set defined for the hmAgentPortType object. This object represents the administratively-configured type of the MAU. If auto-negotiation is not enabled or is not implemented for this MAU, the value of this object determines the operational type of the MAU. In this case, a set to this object will force the MAU into the specified operating mode. If auto-negotiation is implemented and enabled for this MAU, the operational type of the MAU is determined by auto-negotiation, and the value of this object denotes the type to which the MAU will automatically revert if/when auto-negotiation is later disabled. The valid values for this object are: dot3MauType10BaseTHD dot3MauType10BaseTFD dot3MauType100BaseTXHD dot3MauType100BaseTXFD dot3MauType100BaseFXFD dot3MauType1000BaseSXFD

hmAgentPortType.name: hmAgentPortType
hmAgentPortType.description: This object identifies the port type. An initial set of MAU types are defined in RFC 2668. The assignment of OBJECT IDENTIFIERs to new types of MAUs is managed by the IANA. If the MAU type is unknown, the object identifier unknownMauType OBJECT IDENTIFIER ::= { 0 0 } is returned. Note that unknownMauType is a syntactically valid object identifier, and any conformant implementation of ASN.1 and the BER must be able to generate and recognize this value. This object represents the operational type of the MAU, as determined by either (1) the result of the auto-negotiation function or (2) if auto-negotiation is not enabled or is not implemented for this MAU, by the value of the object hmAgentPortDefaultType, or (3) for the GigE card a value determined by the GBIC connected to the card. In case (2), a set to the object hmAgentPortDefaultType will force the MAU into the new operating mode. The valid values for this object are: dot3MauType10BaseTHD dot3MauType10BaseTFD dot3MauType100BaseTXHD dot3MauType100BaseTXFD dot3MauType100BaseFXFD dot3MauType1000BaseSXFD dot3MauType1000BaseTFD

hmAgentPortDVlanTagMode.description: Controls the Double Vlan Tag mode on this port. Default is normal(2).

hmAgentPortDVlanTagEthertype.name: hmAgentPortDVlanTagEthertype
hmAgentPortDVlanTagEthertype.description: Configures the Double Vlan Tag Ethertype for this port. If this object is supported, ethertype cannot be configured globally for the switch. Commonly used are the Ethertypes for vman tags (34984, or 0x88A8) and dot1q tags (33024, or 0x8100).

hmAgentPortDVlanTagCustomerId.name: hmAgentPortDVlanTagCustomerId
hmAgentPortDVlanTagCustomerId.description: Configures the Customer ID for the Double Vlan Tag for this port.

hmAgentPortMaxFrameSizeLimit.name: hmAgentPortMaxFrameSizeLimit
hmAgentPortMaxFrameSizeLimit.description: This object identifies the largest value that can be configured for hmAgentPortMaxFrameSize

hmAgentPortMaxFrameSize.name: hmAgentPortMaxFrameSize
hmAgentPortMaxFrameSize.description: This object identifies the currently configured maximum frame size value for this port. The maximmum value that this object can be set to is the value of hmAgentPortMaxFrameSizeLimit. For Ethernet ports which support 802.1Q vlan tagging, the minimum value that this object can be set to is 1522

hmAgentPortVoiceVlanMode.name: hmAgentPortVoiceVlanMode
hmAgentPortVoiceVlanMode.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN Mode.

hmAgentPortVoiceVlanID.name: hmAgentPortVoiceVlanID
hmAgentPortVoiceVlanID.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN ID if the Voice Vlan Mode is Vlan ID.

hmAgentPortVoiceVlanPriority.name: hmAgentPortVoiceVlanPriority
hmAgentPortVoiceVlanPriority.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN Priority if the Voice Vlan Mode is dot1p. A value of 255 indicates that the priority is not configured.

hmAgentPortVoiceVlanDataPriorityMode.name: hmAgentPortVoiceVlanDataPriorityMode
hmAgentPortVoiceVlanDataPriorityMode.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN Data Priority Mode.

hmAgentPortVoiceVlanOperationalStatus.name: hmAgentPortVoiceVlanOperationalStatus
hmAgentPortVoiceVlanOperationalStatus.description: Describes the Port Voice VLAN Operational Status.

hmAgentPortVoiceVlanDSCP.name: hmAgentPortVoiceVlanDSCP
hmAgentPortVoiceVlanDSCP.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN DSCP value.

hmAgentPortVoiceVlanAuthMode.name: hmAgentPortVoiceVlanAuthMode
hmAgentPortVoiceVlanAuthMode.description: Describes and Configures the Port Voice VLAN Authentication mode. Disable means authentication not required for voice devices when dot1x is enabled.

hmAgentProtocolGroupCreate.name: hmAgentProtocolGroupCreate
hmAgentProtocolGroupCreate.description: Set to non-empty string to create a Protocol-Based VLAN group.

hmAgentProtocolGroupTable.name: hmAgentProtocolGroupTable
hmAgentProtocolGroupTable.description: A table of the switch's Protocol-based VLAN entries

hmAgentProtocolGroupId.name: hmAgentProtocolGroupId
hmAgentProtocolGroupId.description: Group identifier of the Protocol-based VLAN entry.

hmAgentProtocolGroupName.name: hmAgentProtocolGroupName
hmAgentProtocolGroupName.description: Group name of the Protocol-based VLAN entry.

hmAgentProtocolGroupVlanId.name: hmAgentProtocolGroupVlanId
hmAgentProtocolGroupVlanId.description: VLAN associated with the Protocol-based VLAN entry. Set to 0 to remove.

hmAgentProtocolGroupProtocolIP.name: hmAgentProtocolGroupProtocolIP
hmAgentProtocolGroupProtocolIP.description: The status of the IP protocol association with the Protocol-based VLAN entry.

hmAgentProtocolGroupProtocolARP.name: hmAgentProtocolGroupProtocolARP
hmAgentProtocolGroupProtocolARP.description: The status of the ARP protocol association with the Protocol-based VLAN entry.

hmAgentProtocolGroupProtocolIPX.name: hmAgentProtocolGroupProtocolIPX
hmAgentProtocolGroupProtocolIPX.description: The status of the IPX protocol association with the Protocol-based VLAN entry.

hmAgentProtocolGroupStatus.name: hmAgentProtocolGroupStatus
hmAgentProtocolGroupStatus.description: The status of the Protocol-based VLAN entry. active(1) - this entry is active destroy(6) - remove this entry

hmAgentProtocolGroupPortTable.name: hmAgentProtocolGroupPortTable
hmAgentProtocolGroupPortTable.description: A table of the switch's physical port config entries

hmAgentProtocolGroupPortIfIndex.name: hmAgentProtocolGroupPortIfIndex
hmAgentProtocolGroupPortIfIndex.description: The interface number of this instance.

hmAgentProtocolGroupPortStatus.name: hmAgentProtocolGroupPortStatus
hmAgentProtocolGroupPortStatus.description: The status of this entry. active(1) - the port is associated with this group createAndGo(4) - add the port to this group createAndWait(5) - add the port to this group destroy(6) - remove the port from this group

hmAgentStpConfigFormatSelector.name: hmAgentStpConfigFormatSelector
hmAgentStpConfigFormatSelector.description: The MST configuration format selector. A value other than 0 (zero) indicates non-support for the IEEE 802.1s standard.

hmAgentStpConfigName.name: hmAgentStpConfigName
hmAgentStpConfigName.description: The MST configuration name of at most 32 characters.

hmAgentStpConfigRevision.name: hmAgentStpConfigRevision
hmAgentStpConfigRevision.description: The MST configuration revision. The default value is 1.

hmAgentStpForceVersion.name: hmAgentStpForceVersion
hmAgentStpForceVersion.description: The MST configuration force protocol version. The default version is dot1w.

hmAgentStpAdminMode.name: hmAgentStpAdminMode
hmAgentStpAdminMode.description: The spanning tree operational status. enable(1) - enables spanning tree operational status on the switch. disable(2) - disables spanning tree operational status on the switch. The default status is enabled.

hmAgentStpBpduGuardMode.name: hmAgentStpBpduGuardMode
hmAgentStpBpduGuardMode.description: The spanning tree BPDU Guard Mode. enable(1) - enables BPDU Guard Mode on the switch. disable(2) - disables BPDU Guard Mode on the switch. The default status is disabled.

hmAgentStpBpduFilterDefault.name: hmAgentStpBpduFilterDefault
hmAgentStpBpduFilterDefault.description: The spanning tree BPDU Filter Mode, it enables BPDU Filter on all edge ports. enable(1) - enables BPDU Filter Mode on the switch. disable(2) - disables BPDU Filter Mode on the switch. The default status is disabled.

hmAgentStpPortState.name: hmAgentStpPortState
hmAgentStpPortState.description: The administrative STP state for the port. enable(1) - enables STP on the port. disable(2) - disables STP on the port. The default port STP state is enabled for the first 4095 ports and disabled for any ports beyond.

hmAgentStpPortStatsMstpBpduRx.name: hmAgentStpPortStatsMstpBpduRx
hmAgentStpPortStatsMstpBpduRx.description: The MSTP BPDUs received on a specific port.

hmAgentStpPortStatsMstpBpduTx.name: hmAgentStpPortStatsMstpBpduTx
hmAgentStpPortStatsMstpBpduTx.description: The MSTP BPDUs sent from a specific port.

hmAgentStpPortStatsRstpBpduRx.name: hmAgentStpPortStatsRstpBpduRx
hmAgentStpPortStatsRstpBpduRx.description: The RSTP BPDUs received on a specific port.

hmAgentStpPortStatsRstpBpduTx.name: hmAgentStpPortStatsRstpBpduTx
hmAgentStpPortStatsRstpBpduTx.description: The RSTP BPDUs sent from a specific port.

hmAgentStpPortStatsStpBpduRx.name: hmAgentStpPortStatsStpBpduRx
hmAgentStpPortStatsStpBpduRx.description: The STP BPDUs received on a specific port.

hmAgentStpPortStatsStpBpduTx.name: hmAgentStpPortStatsStpBpduTx
hmAgentStpPortStatsStpBpduTx.description: The STP BPDUs sent from a specific port.

hmAgentStpPortUpTime.name: hmAgentStpPortUpTime
hmAgentStpPortUpTime.description: Time since port was reset. It is displayed in days, hours, minutes, and seconds.

hmAgentStpPortMigrationCheck.name: hmAgentStpPortMigrationCheck
hmAgentStpPortMigrationCheck.description: Force the specified port to transmit RSTP or MSTP BPDU's. Supported values: false(0) - BPDUs are not to be transmitted. true(1) - BPDUs are to be transmitted A non-zero value indicates that BPDUs are to be sent on the specified port.

hmAgentStpPortHelloTime.name: hmAgentStpPortHelloTime
hmAgentStpPortHelloTime.description: Hello time for the STP port. The default value is 2.

hmAgentStpCstHelloTime.name: hmAgentStpCstHelloTime
hmAgentStpCstHelloTime.description: The MSTP root port hello time for the CIST.

hmAgentStpCstMaxAge.name: hmAgentStpCstMaxAge
hmAgentStpCstMaxAge.description: The MSTP root port max age for the CIST.

hmAgentStpCstRegionalRootId.name: hmAgentStpCstRegionalRootId
hmAgentStpCstRegionalRootId.description: The MSTP regional root identifier for the CIST.

hmAgentStpCstRegionalRootPathCost.name: hmAgentStpCstRegionalRootPathCost
hmAgentStpCstRegionalRootPathCost.description: The MSTP regional root path cost for the CIST.

hmAgentStpCstRootFwdDelay.name: hmAgentStpCstRootFwdDelay
hmAgentStpCstRootFwdDelay.description: The MSTP root port forward delay for the CIST.

hmAgentStpCstBridgeFwdDelay.name: hmAgentStpCstBridgeFwdDelay
hmAgentStpCstBridgeFwdDelay.description: The MSTP bridge forward delay for the CIST. The default value is 15.

hmAgentStpCstBridgeHelloTime.name: hmAgentStpCstBridgeHelloTime
hmAgentStpCstBridgeHelloTime.description: The MSTP bridge hello time for the CIST. The default value is 2.

hmAgentStpCstBridgeHoldTime.name: hmAgentStpCstBridgeHoldTime
hmAgentStpCstBridgeHoldTime.description: The MSTP bridge hold time for the CIST.

hmAgentStpCstBridgeMaxAge.name: hmAgentStpCstBridgeMaxAge
hmAgentStpCstBridgeMaxAge.description: The MSTP bridge max age for the CIST. The default value is 20.

hmAgentStpCstBridgeDesignatedRoot.name: hmAgentStpCstBridgeDesignatedRoot
hmAgentStpCstBridgeDesignatedRoot.description: The Designated Root like in dot1dStpDesignatedRoot.

hmAgentStpCstBridgePriority.name: hmAgentStpCstBridgePriority
hmAgentStpCstBridgePriority.description: The MSTP bridge priority for the CIST. The default value is 32768.

hmAgentStpCstBridgeTimeSinceTopologyChan.name: hmAgentStpCstBridgeTimeSinceTopologyChange
hmAgentStpCstBridgeTimeSinceTopologyChan.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since the last time a topology change was detected by the bridge entity.

hmAgentStpCstBridgeTopChanges.name: hmAgentStpCstBridgeTopChanges
hmAgentStpCstBridgeTopChanges.description: The total number of topology changes detected by this bridge since the management entity was last reset or initialized.

hmAgentStpCstBridgeRootCost.name: hmAgentStpCstBridgeRootCost
hmAgentStpCstBridgeRootCost.description: The cost of the path to the root as seen from this bridge.

hmAgentStpCstBridgeRootPort.name: hmAgentStpCstBridgeRootPort
hmAgentStpCstBridgeRootPort.description: The port number of the port which offers the lowest cost path from this bridge to the root bridge.

hmAgentStpCstBridgeMaxHops.name: hmAgentStpCstBridgeMaxHops
hmAgentStpCstBridgeMaxHops.description: The MSTP bridge max hops for the CIST. The default value is 20.

hmAgentStpCstBridgeHoldCount.name: hmAgentStpCstBridgeHoldCount
hmAgentStpCstBridgeHoldCount.description: The MSTP bridge hold count for the CIST. This command sets the value of maximum bpdus that a bridge is allowed to send within a hello time window. The default value is 10.

hmAgentStpCstPortOperEdge.name: hmAgentStpCstPortOperEdge
hmAgentStpCstPortOperEdge.description: The MSTP operational status of a specific port for the CIST.

hmAgentStpCstPortOperPointToPoint.name: hmAgentStpCstPortOperPointToPoint
hmAgentStpCstPortOperPointToPoint.description: The MSTP operational point to point mac of a specific port for the CIST.

hmAgentStpCstPortTopologyChangeAck.name: hmAgentStpCstPortTopologyChangeAck
hmAgentStpCstPortTopologyChangeAck.description: The MSTP topology change acknowledge for a specific port in the CIST.

hmAgentStpCstPortEdge.name: hmAgentStpCstPortEdge
hmAgentStpCstPortEdge.description: The administrative state of a specific port in CIST. true(1) - port is edge port. false(2) - port is auto-edge or no edge port. The default port state is disabled.

hmAgentStpCstPortForwardingState.name: hmAgentStpCstPortForwardingState
hmAgentStpCstPortForwardingState.description: The MSTP forwarding state of a specific port in CIST.

hmAgentStpCstPortId.name: hmAgentStpCstPortId
hmAgentStpCstPortId.description: The MSTP port identifier of a specific port in CIST.

hmAgentStpCstPortPathCost.name: hmAgentStpCstPortPathCost
hmAgentStpCstPortPathCost.description: The MSTP port path cost in CIST. The default value will correspond to the recommendation specified in IEEE 802.1s Table 13-2 which varies depending upon link speed.

hmAgentStpCstPortPriority.name: hmAgentStpCstPortPriority
hmAgentStpCstPortPriority.description: The MSTP port priority in CIST. The priority is in the increments of 16. The default value is 128.

hmAgentStpCstDesignatedBridgeId.name: hmAgentStpCstDesignatedBridgeId
hmAgentStpCstDesignatedBridgeId.description: The MSTP designated bridge ID of a specific port in CIST.

hmAgentStpCstDesignatedCost.name: hmAgentStpCstDesignatedCost
hmAgentStpCstDesignatedCost.description: The MSTP designated cost of a specific port in CIST.

hmAgentStpCstDesignatedPortId.name: hmAgentStpCstDesignatedPortId
hmAgentStpCstDesignatedPortId.description: The MSTP designated port ID of a specific port in CIST.

hmAgentStpCstExtPortPathCost.name: hmAgentStpCstExtPortPathCost
hmAgentStpCstExtPortPathCost.description: The MSTP external port path cost in CIST. The default value varies depending upon the link speed.

hmAgentStpCstPortAutoEdge.name: hmAgentStpCstPortAutoEdge
hmAgentStpCstPortAutoEdge.description: The auto edge state of a specific port in CIST. true(1) - enables the port. false(2) - disables the port. The default port state is enabled.

hmAgentStpCstPortRole.name: hmAgentStpCstPortRole
hmAgentStpCstPortRole.description: The current Port Role for the Port (i.e., Root, Alternate, Designated, or Backup), for the CIST.

hmAgentStpCstPortDisputed.name: hmAgentStpCstPortDisputed
hmAgentStpCstPortDisputed.description: The current value of the disputed variable for the CIST for the Port. A value of true(1) indicates that the disputed variable is set. A value of false(2) indicates that the agreed variable is cleared.

hmAgentStpCstPortBpduGuardEffect.name: hmAgentStpCstPortBpduGuardEffect
hmAgentStpCstPortBpduGuardEffect.description: BPDU Guard Mode effect on the port. enable(1) - BPDU Guard Mode is enabled on the port. disable(2) - BPDU Guard Mode is disabled on the port.

hmAgentStpCstPortBpduFilter.name: hmAgentStpCstPortBpduFilter
hmAgentStpCstPortBpduFilter.description: This command sets BPDU Filter mode on the port. enable(1) - BPDU Filter Mode is enabled on the port. disable(2) - BPDU Filter Mode is disabled on the port.

hmAgentStpCstPortBpduFlood.name: hmAgentStpCstPortBpduFlood
hmAgentStpCstPortBpduFlood.description: This command sets BPDU Flood mode on the port. enable(1) - BPDU Flood Mode is enabled on the port. disable(2) - BPDU Flood Mode is disabled on the port.

hmAgentStpCstPortRootGuard.name: hmAgentStpCstPortRootGuard
hmAgentStpCstPortRootGuard.description: This command sets a port to discard any superior information received by the port and thus protect against root of the device from changing.The port gets put into discarding state and does not forward any packets. enable(1) - enables the root-guard mode for the port. disable(2) - disables the root-guard mode for the port. The default root-guard mode is disabled.

hmAgentStpCstPortTCNGuard.name: hmAgentStpCstPortTCNGuard
hmAgentStpCstPortTCNGuard.description: This command restricts the port from propagating any topology change information received through that port. enable(1) - enables the tcn-guard mode for the port. disable(2) - disables the tcn-guard mode for the port. The default tcn-guard mode is disabled.

hmAgentStpCstPortLoopGuard.name: hmAgentStpCstPortLoopGuard
hmAgentStpCstPortLoopGuard.description: This command enables loop guard on this port. This setting applies to all Spanning Tree instances of which this port is a member. enable(1) - enables the loop guard mode for the port. disable(2) - disables the loop guard mode for the port. The default loop-guard mode is disabled.

hmAgentStpMstBridgePriority.name: hmAgentStpMstBridgePriority
hmAgentStpMstBridgePriority.description: The MSTP bridge priority in a specific instance. The priority is in the increments of 4096. The recommended default value is 32768.

hmAgentStpMstBridgeIdentifier.name: hmAgentStpMstBridgeIdentifier
hmAgentStpMstBridgeIdentifier.description: The MSTP bridge identifier in a specific instance.

hmAgentStpMstDesignatedRootId.name: hmAgentStpMstDesignatedRootId
hmAgentStpMstDesignatedRootId.description: The MSTP designated root bridge identifier in a specific instance.

hmAgentStpMstRootPathCost.name: hmAgentStpMstRootPathCost
hmAgentStpMstRootPathCost.description: The MSTP root path cost in a specific instance.

hmAgentStpMstRootPortId.name: hmAgentStpMstRootPortId
hmAgentStpMstRootPortId.description: The MSTP root port ID in a specific instance.

hmAgentStpMstTimeSinceTopologyChange.name: hmAgentStpMstTimeSinceTopologyChange
hmAgentStpMstTimeSinceTopologyChange.description: The MSTP time since the last topology change in a specific instance.

hmAgentStpMstTopologyChangeCount.name: hmAgentStpMstTopologyChangeCount
hmAgentStpMstTopologyChangeCount.description: The MSTP count of topology changes in a specific instance.

hmAgentStpMstTopologyChangeParm.name: hmAgentStpMstTopologyChangeParm
hmAgentStpMstTopologyChangeParm.description: The MSTP topology change parameter in a specific instance.

hmAgentStpMstRowStatus.name: hmAgentStpMstRowStatus
hmAgentStpMstRowStatus.description: The MSTP instance status. Supported values: active(1) - valid instance. createAndGo(4) - used to create a new instance. destroy(6) - removes an instance.

hmAgentStpMstPortForwardingState.name: hmAgentStpMstPortForwardingState
hmAgentStpMstPortForwardingState.description: The MSTP forwarding state of a specific port in a specific instance.

hmAgentStpMstPortId.name: hmAgentStpMstPortId
hmAgentStpMstPortId.description: The MSTP port identifier of a specific port in a specific instance.

hmAgentStpMstPortPathCost.name: hmAgentStpMstPortPathCost
hmAgentStpMstPortPathCost.description: The MSTP port path cost in a specific instance. The default value will correspond to the recommendation specified in IEEE 802.1s Table 13-2 which varies depending upon link speed.

hmAgentStpMstPortPriority.name: hmAgentStpMstPortPriority
hmAgentStpMstPortPriority.description: The MSTP port priority in a specific instance. The priority is in the increments of 16. The default value is 128.

hmAgentStpMstDesignatedBridgeId.name: hmAgentStpMstDesignatedBridgeId
hmAgentStpMstDesignatedBridgeId.description: The MSTP designated bridge ID of a specific port in a specific instance.

hmAgentStpMstDesignatedCost.name: hmAgentStpMstDesignatedCost
hmAgentStpMstDesignatedCost.description: The MSTP designated cost of a specific port in a specific instance.

hmAgentStpMstDesignatedPortId.name: hmAgentStpMstDesignatedPortId
hmAgentStpMstDesignatedPortId.description: The MSTP designated port ID of a specific port in a specific instance.

hmAgentStpMstPortRole.name: hmAgentStpMstPortRole
hmAgentStpMstPortRole.description: In an MSTP Bridge, the current Port Role for the Port (i.e., Root, Alternate, Designated, or Backup), for the MSTI.

hmAgentStpMstPortDisputed.name: hmAgentStpMstPortDisputed
hmAgentStpMstPortDisputed.description: In an MSTP Bridge, the current value of the disputed variable for the MSTI for the Port.

hmAgentStpMstPortLoopInconsistentState.name: hmAgentStpMstPortLoopInconsistentState
hmAgentStpMstPortLoopInconsistentState.description: The loop inconsistent state of a specific port in a specific instance. This value can only report as true(1) when loop guard is enabled on the port and the port has transitioned from blocking state in this MST instance.

hmAgentStpMstPortTransitionsIntoLoopInco.name: hmAgentStpMstPortTransitionsIntoLoopInconsistentState
hmAgentStpMstPortTransitionsIntoLoopInco.description: The number of times this interface has transitioned into loop inconsistent state.

hmAgentStpMstPortTransitionsOutOfLoopInc.name: hmAgentStpMstPortTransitionsOutOfLoopInconsistentState
hmAgentStpMstPortTransitionsOutOfLoopInc.description: The number of times this interface has transitioned out of loop inconsistent state.

hmAgentStpMstReceivedBridgeId.name: hmAgentStpMstReceivedBridgeId
hmAgentStpMstReceivedBridgeId.description: The MSTP received bridge ID on a specific port in a specific instance.

hmAgentStpMstReceivedRPC.name: hmAgentStpMstReceivedRPC
hmAgentStpMstReceivedRPC.description: The MSTP received root path cost of a specific port in a specific instance.

hmAgentStpMstReceivedPortId.name: hmAgentStpMstReceivedPortId
hmAgentStpMstReceivedPortId.description: The MSTP received port ID on a specific port in a specific instance.

hmAgentStpMstVlanRowStatus.name: hmAgentStpMstVlanRowStatus
hmAgentStpMstVlanRowStatus.description: The association status of an MSTP instance and a VLAN. Supported values: active(1) - valid association between an MSTP instance and a VLAN. createAndGo(4) - used to create a new association between an MSTP instance and a VLAN. destroy(6) - removes the association between an MSTP instance and a VLAN.

hmAgentClassOfServicePortTable.name: hmAgentClassOfServicePortTable
hmAgentClassOfServicePortTable.description: A table that contains information about the 802.1p priority mapping to traffic class priority queue for every physical port.

hmAgentClassOfServicePortEntry.name: hmAgentClassOfServicePortEntry
hmAgentClassOfServicePortEntry.description: A 802.1p priority mapped to a traffic class priority queue.

hmAgentClassOfServicePortPriority.name: hmAgentClassOfServicePortPriority
hmAgentClassOfServicePortPriority.description: The Priority value determined for the received frame. This value is equivalent to the priority indicated in the tagged frame received, or one of the evaluated priorities, determined according to the media-type. For untagged frames received from Ethernet media, this value is equal to the dot1dPortDefaultUserPriority value for the ingress port.

hmAgentClassOfServicePortClass.name: hmAgentClassOfServicePortClass
hmAgentClassOfServicePortClass.description: Traffic class priority queue the received frame is mapped to. The possible range depends on the number of supported traffic classes for the appropriate port, as shown in dot1dPortNumTrafficClasses.

hmAgentSaveConfig.name: hmAgentSaveConfig
hmAgentSaveConfig.description: Enable hmAgentSaveConfig will initiate an configuration save to nvram. Disable hmAgentSaveConfig after a configuration save will reset hmAgentSaveConfigStatus back to notInitiated state.

hmAgentSaveConfigStatus.name: hmAgentSaveConfigStatus
hmAgentSaveConfigStatus.description: Indicates the current status of an save configuration request.

hmAgentCableTesterStatus.name: hmAgentCableTesterStatus
hmAgentCableTesterStatus.description: Status of the Virtual Cable Tester active(1) - cable testing is in progress. Set to this value to start the test. success(2) - A successful test was performed. Cannot be set. failure(3) - A failure was encountered during the test. Cannot be set. uninitialized(4) - No test has been performed yet. Cannot be set.

hmAgentCableTesterIfIndex.name: hmAgentCableTesterIfIndex
hmAgentCableTesterIfIndex.description: Determines on which port to perform the cable test. Limited to copper based ports.

hmAgentCableTesterCableStatus.name: hmAgentCableTesterCableStatus
hmAgentCableTesterCableStatus.description: Indicates the results of the Cable Test. normal(1) - The cable is working correctly. open(2) - The cable is disconnected or there is a faulty connector. short(3) - There is an electrical short in the cable. unknown(4) - No test has been performed yet, or a test is currently in progress.

hmAgentCableTesterMinimumCableLength.name: hmAgentCableTesterMinimumCableLength
hmAgentCableTesterMinimumCableLength.description: The estimated length of the cable in meters. This value indicates the shortest length estimated. This object will return 0 if hmAgentCableTesterStatus is not success(2) or the cable length is unknown.

hmAgentCableTesterMaximumCableLength.name: hmAgentCableTesterMaximumCableLength
hmAgentCableTesterMaximumCableLength.description: The estimated length of the cable in meters. This value indicates the longest length estimated. This object will return 0 if hmAgentCableTesterStatus is not success(2) or the cable length is unknown.

hmAgentCableTesterCableFailureLocation.name: hmAgentCableTesterCableFailureLocation
hmAgentCableTesterCableFailureLocation.description: The estimated distance in meters from the end of the cable to the failure location. This object will return 0 if hmAgentCableTesterStatus is not success(2).

hmAgentSSHAdminMode.name: hmAgentSSHAdminMode
hmAgentSSHAdminMode.description: Configures whether the SSH service is enabled on this switch. The default value is disable(2).

hmAgentSSHProtocolLevel.name: hmAgentSSHProtocolLevel
hmAgentSSHProtocolLevel.description: Configures which protocol versions of SSH are enabled on this switch. The default value is both(3).

hmAgentSSHSessionsCount.name: hmAgentSSHSessionsCount
hmAgentSSHSessionsCount.description: Current number of active SSH sessions on this switch.

hmAgentSSHMaxSessionsCount.name: hmAgentSSHMaxSessionsCount
hmAgentSSHMaxSessionsCount.description: Max number of SSH sessions permitted on this switch.

hmAgentSSHSessionTimeout.name: hmAgentSSHSessionTimeout
hmAgentSSHSessionTimeout.description: ssh idle timeout value for this switch im minutes.

hmAgentRadiusMaxTransmit.name: hmAgentRadiusMaxTransmit
hmAgentRadiusMaxTransmit.description: Maximum number of retransmissions of a RADIUS request packet

hmAgentRadiusTimeout.name: hmAgentRadiusTimeout
hmAgentRadiusTimeout.description: Time out duration (in seconds) before packets are retransmitted

hmAgentRadiusAccountingMode.name: hmAgentRadiusAccountingMode
hmAgentRadiusAccountingMode.description: Identifies if RADIUS Accounting has been enabled or not

hmAgentRadiusStatsClear.name: hmAgentRadiusStatsClear
hmAgentRadiusStatsClear.description: When set to enable(1), all Radius statistics will be reset.

hmAgentRadiusAccountingIndexNextValid.name: hmAgentRadiusAccountingIndexNextValid
hmAgentRadiusAccountingIndexNextValid.description: Indicates the next valid index into the hmAgentRadiusAccountingConfigTable for creation. If no additional entries are allowed, this will be 0.

hmAgentRadiusAccountingConfigTable.name: hmAgentRadiusAccountingConfigTable
hmAgentRadiusAccountingConfigTable.description: Table with information about Radius Accounting Server IP Addresses, port numbers and shared secret. Only one entry is supported at this time.

hmAgentRadiusAccountingConfigEntry.name: hmAgentRadiusAccountingConfigEntry
hmAgentRadiusAccountingConfigEntry.description: Entry consisting of configuration data for a Radius Accounting Server.

hmAgentRadiusAccountingServerIndex.name: hmAgentRadiusAccountingServerIndex
hmAgentRadiusAccountingServerIndex.description: Unique index of the configured RADIUS accounting server. The next valid value of this object for creation is specified by hmAgentRadiusAccountingIndexNextValid.

hmAgentRadiusAccountingServerAddress.name: hmAgentRadiusAccountingServerAddress
hmAgentRadiusAccountingServerAddress.description: IP Address of the configured RADIUS accounting server. This object cannot be changed after creation.

hmAgentRadiusAccountingPort.name: hmAgentRadiusAccountingPort
hmAgentRadiusAccountingPort.description: Port number for the RADIUS accounting server.

hmAgentRadiusAccountingSecret.name: hmAgentRadiusAccountingSecret
hmAgentRadiusAccountingSecret.description: Configured shared sercret for the RADIUS accounting server.

hmAgentRadiusAccountingStatus.name: hmAgentRadiusAccountingStatus
hmAgentRadiusAccountingStatus.description: Creates or destroys a RADIUS accounting server entry.
